 To simplify the given expression, we can combine like terms. We have:

\begin{align*}
(9x^9+7x^8+4x^7)+(x^{11}+x^9+2x^7+3x^3+5x+8) &= x^{11} + (9x^9 + x^9) + 7x^8 + (4x^7 + 2x^7) + 3x^3 + 5x + 8 \\
&= x^{11} + 10x^9 + 7x^8 + 6x^7 + 3x^3 + 5x + 8.
\end{align*}

<answer> $x^{11} + 10x^9 + 7x^8 + 6x^7 + 3x^3 + 5x + 8$ </answer>

